The Master Context: The Thread of the Down
The Theme: "The Watchers of the Down" (1862–2033).
The Interlink: The Fort is a stationary observer. The technology changes from Flint ➔ Copper ➔ Radar ➔ Silicon, but the "Pilot" at the helm remains the human heart.
Character 1: The Architect of Invariants (1871)
Persona: Captain of the 103rd Regiment (Royal Bombay Fusiliers)
The Story: He arrives from the Indian Mutiny to the cold chalk of the Down. He is obsessed with the Physics of the 7-inch Armstrong Gun. To him, the Fort isn't a "Folly"; it is a mathematical certainty designed to refuse the French.
Unique AI Manifestation (Julian’s Lens):
The Invariant: We use LiDAR data to show the Captain’s world as a perfect geometric wireframe.
The Visual: A Veo 3.1 "Heal" where the modern mud of the parade ground is swept away in 1.2ms to reveal his pristine 1871 drill formation.
The Interlink: He is the one who sets the Sovereign Canon that Kiddle will follow 70 years later.
